BRIEFLY 
Time Warner Cable Chief Named: Time Warner Inc. announced that, as expected, 
Joseph J. Collins would head its cable division, which will be called the Time 
Warner Cable Group. The company is the nation's second-largest cable system 
operator. Time Inc. and Warner Communications Inc. had said when they announced 
plans to merge last March that Collins, the chairman and chief executive of 
Time's 82%-owned American Television &amp; Communications Corp., would head 
their combined cable operations. Collins will retain his posts at the Stamford, 
Conn.-based ATC as well as become chairman and president of Time Warner Cable 
Group. 
